By Ejike Ejike, Abuja The Inspector-General of Police, IGP Mohammed Adamu, has given posthumous promotion to 16 policemen killed during the #EndSARS protest. The IGP, while congratulating the officers, charged them to see their promotion as a mark of additional responsibility and a call to rededicate themselves to their professional calling.  Mba further noted that “the IGP promised to work with all relevant agencies, organs of government and other stakeholders in driving a successful reform of the Police for improved welfare and conditions of service towards better service delivery to the people.”